OL,3,CDeborah James' mum hails bowel cancer
OL,4,Cscreening age extension
OL,6,FHeather James, the mother of Dame
OL,7,FDeborah James who died of bowel cancer
OL,8,Faged 40 in 2022, has hailed the
OL,9,Fextension of bowel cancer screening
OL,10,Ftests.
OL,12,FThe NHS announced that around 850,000
OL,13,Fmore people will receive bowel cancer
OL,14,Ftesting kits as part of its screening
OL,15,Fscheme in England.
OL,17,FThe current programme covers people
OL,18,Faged 54 to 74, but the expansion means
OL,19,Feveryone aged 50 to 74 will eventually
OL,20,Fbe offered a home-screening test to
OL,21,Fhelp detect bowel cancer.
