OL,3,CDeborah James' mum hails bowel cancer
OL,4,Cscreening age extension
OL,6,FProfessor Peter Johnson, national
OL,7,Fclinical director for cancer at NHS
OL,8,FEngland, said: "There is no need to
OL,9,Ffeel embarrassed about poo - the test
OL,10,Fis quick and simple to use and can
OL,11,Fdetect signs of bowel cancer, often
OL,12,Fbefore symptoms appear".
OL,14,FWhile the bowel cancer screening
OL,15,Fprogramme will cover those aged 50 to
OL,16,F74, anyone aged 75 and over can
OL,17,Frequest a kit by phoning the NHS bowel
OL,18,Fcancer screening helpline on 0800 707
OL,19,F60 60.
